OL,3,CTeachers 'reluctant to use AI for
OL,4,Cpupil learning and assessment'
OL,6,FThe survey, which covered 2,000
OL,7,Fsecondary schools in England, found
OL,8,Fthat 84% of those asked have not
OL,9,Fchanged the way they assess their
OL,10,Fstudents' work, despite the widespread
OL,11,Favailability of AI tools, and only 41%
OL,12,Fsaid they were regularly checking
OL,13,Fhomework or coursework for plagiarised
OL,14,Fcontent from the web, served up by AI
OL,15,Ftools.
OL,17,FIn its report, BCS calls for the
OL,18,Funderstanding of AI to be made a
OL,19,Fsignificant part of teacher training,
OL,20,Falongside wider digital literacy.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/7
