OL,3,CTeachers 'reluctant to use AI for
OL,4,Cpupil learning and assessment'
OL,6,FThe IT body said schools should also
OL,7,Fget AI policies in place and publish
OL,8,Fthem on their websites, but that clear
OL,9,Fguidance on the issue is first needed
OL,10,Ffrom the Department for Education,
OL,11,Fqualifications regulator Ofqual and
OL,12,Fother bodies.
OL,14,FJulia Adamson, managing director for
OL,15,Feducation and public benefit at BCS,
OL,16,Fsaid: "Teachers see the opportunity AI
OL,17,Fpresents to transform their work and
OL,18,Fthe lives of their students, from
OL,19,Fsaving time on lesson plans, to
OL,20,Fpersonalising learning for each young
OL,21,Fperson.
