OL,3,CTeachers 'reluctant to use AI for
OL,4,Cpupil learning and assessment'
OL,6,F"It is understandable that school
OL,7,Fleaders and teachers need training and
OL,8,Fguidance in order to feel confident
OL,9,Fusing AI. It is also true that no AI
OL,10,Ftool is infallible or can replace the
OL,11,Fjudgement and knowledge of a human
OL,12,Fexpert. There are also lots of
OL,13,Fsafeguarding and ethical
OL,14,Fconsiderations around use of this
OL,15,Ftechnology.
OL,17,F"It therefore makes sense that AI is
OL,18,Fintroduced gradually in order to
OL,19,Fmaximise its potential and mitigate
OL,20,Fthe risks."
